the locale is local  languages displayed
	first  compiled by locale-gen with conf file as locale.gen in /etc
	then check by locale -a 
	then you choose one as default  and set  LANG="XXX" in /etc/locale.conf or just localectl set-locale LANG=XXX


differences  among keymaps  font  locale
	the keymaps  control  the keys input
	the font  controls  the font type  utf8 bge ...
	the locale  controls  which  language is displayed , is the most  overalled



	
